abstract: Donald Trump on Tuesday used his State of the Union speech to award the highest U.S. civilian honor to polarizing radio show host Rush Limbaugh in one of several attention-grabbing moments staged by the former reality TV star-turned-president.
snippet: Donald Trump on Tuesday used his State of the Union speech to award the highest U.S. civilian honor to polarizing radio show host Rush Limbaugh in one of several attention-grabbing moments staged by the former reality TV star-turned-president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Donald Trump on Tuesday used his State of the Union speech to award the highest U.S. civilian honor to polarizing radio show host Rush Limbaugh in one of several attention-grabbing moments staged by the former reality TV star-turned-president.
headline_main: Trump the Showman Honors Provocative Talk-Show Host Limbaugh
headline_print_headline: Trump the Showman Honors Provocative Talk-Show Host Limbaugh

abstract: A bitter feud between U.S. President Donald Trump and top Democrat Nancy Pelosi boiled over at his State of the Union speech on Tuesday, with Trump denying her a handshake and Pelosi ripping apart a copy of his remarks behind his back.
snippet: A bitter feud between U.S. President Donald Trump and top Democrat Nancy Pelosi boiled over at his State of the Union speech on Tuesday, with Trump denying her a handshake and Pelosi ripping apart a copy of his remarks behind his back.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A bitter feud between U.S. President Donald Trump and top Democrat Nancy Pelosi boiled over at his State of the Union speech on Tuesday, with Trump denying her a handshake and Pelosi ripping apart a copy of his remarks behind his back.
headline_main: Trump-Pelosi Feud Erupts During Speech to Congress as Impeachment Trial Nears End
headline_print_headline: Trump-Pelosi Feud Erupts During Speech to Congress as Impeachment Trial Nears End

abstract: DERRY, N.H. — Senator Bernie Sanders began his town hall here in Derry on Wednesday morning on a solemn note.
lead_paragraph: DERRY, N.H. — Senator Bernie Sanders began his town hall here in Derry on Wednesday morning on a solemn note.

abstract: Democrats campaigned on healthcare when they won control of the U.S. House of Representatives in 2018. President Donald Trump made plain on Tuesday that he would try to use the issue to his advantage in the 2020 presidential election.
snippet: Democrats campaigned on healthcare when they won control of the U.S. House of Representatives in 2018. President Donald Trump made plain on Tuesday that he would try to use the issue to his advantage in the 2020 presidential election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats campaigned on healthcare when they won control of the U.S. House of Representatives in 2018. President Donald Trump made plain on Tuesday that he would try to use the issue to his advantage in the 2020 presidential election.
headline_main: In Political Speech to Congress, Trump Pokes at Democrats' Divide on Healthcare
headline_print_headline: In Political Speech to Congress, Trump Pokes at Democrats' Divide on Healthcare

abstract: Virginia Democratic-led lawmakers on Tuesday passed a bill to block future oil and gas development off the state's coastline, reflecting opposition to the Republican Trump administration's efforts to open Atlantic waters to fossil fuel exploration.
snippet: Virginia Democratic-led lawmakers on Tuesday passed a bill to block future oil and gas development off the state's coastline, reflecting opposition to the Republican Trump administration's efforts to open Atlantic waters to fossil fuel exploration...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Virginia Democratic-led lawmakers on Tuesday passed a bill to block future oil and gas development off the state's coastline, reflecting opposition to the Republican Trump administration's efforts to open Atlantic waters to fossil fuel exploration.
headline_main: Virginia Lawmakers Vote to Block Offshore Drilling in Rebuke to Trump Plan
headline_print_headline: Virginia Lawmakers Vote to Block Offshore Drilling in Rebuke to Trump Plan

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg on Wednesday nabbed his first endorsement from a governor: Gina Raimondo of Rhode Island.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg on Wednesday nabbed his first endorsement from a governor: Gina Raimondo of Rhode Island.

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg on Tuesday said he will immediately double his already massive nationwide television ad spending and expand his staff after the debacle of Iowa's failure to promptly announce its caucuses results.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg on Tuesday said he will immediately double his already massive nationwide television ad spending and expand his staff after the debacle of Iowa's failure to promptly announce its caucuses results...
lead_paragraph: DETROIT/DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg on Tuesday said he will immediately double his already massive nationwide television ad spending and expand his staff after the debacle of Iowa's failure to promptly announce its caucuses results.
headline_main: Bloomberg to Double TV Spending, Expand Staff After Democrats' Iowa Caucus Chaos
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg to Double TV Spending, Expand Staff After Democrats' Iowa Caucus Chaos

abstract: The Republican-controlled Senate acquitted President Donald Trump on two impeachment charges Wednesday amid Republican complaints about what they called a rushed process and Democratic claims that Trump is a threat to democracy. The historic, three-week trial proceeded largely along partisan lines, with just one senator — Republican Mitt Romney of Utah — breaking with his party.
snippet: The Republican-controlled Senate acquitted President Donald Trump on two impeachment charges Wednesday amid Republican complaints about what they called a rushed process and Democratic claims that Trump is a threat to democracy. The historic, thre...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Republican-controlled Senate acquitted President Donald Trump on two impeachment charges Wednesday amid Republican complaints about what they called a rushed process and Democratic claims that Trump is a threat to democracy. The historic, three-week trial proceeded largely along partisan lines, with just one senator — Republican Mitt Romney of Utah — breaking with his party.
headline_main: Impeachment Takeaways: Trump's Iron Grip, McConnell Delivers
headline_print_headline: Impeachment Takeaways: Trump's Iron Grip, McConnell Delivers

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump displayed reality TV flair on Tuesday to underscore his pledge to wind down the war in Afghanistan, engineering the return of an Army sergeant who surprised his wife and two young children in the House of Representatives as a national broadcast audience looked on.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump displayed reality TV flair on Tuesday to underscore his pledge to wind down the war in Afghanistan, engineering the return of an Army sergeant who surprised his wife and two young children in the House of Representative...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump displayed reality TV flair on Tuesday to underscore his pledge to wind down the war in Afghanistan, engineering the return of an Army sergeant who surprised his wife and two young children in the House of Representatives as a national broadcast audience looked on.
headline_main: With Made-For-TV Flourish, Trump Makes Case for Bringing Troops Home
headline_print_headline: With Made-For-TV Flourish, Trump Makes Case for Bringing Troops Home
